01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:53.128
Keep me safe, keep me safe,
keep me safe!

01:10:53.236 --> 01:10:55.363
<i>Mike, security?</i>

01:10:55.472 --> 01:10:59.374
<i>Mike, do you have any reports of any</i>
<i>missing kids, any missing children?</i>

01:11:00.710 --> 01:11:03.076
- All right, thanks, Mike.
- We should get in there

01:11:03.179 --> 01:11:06.239
Boy. You, boy

01:11:06.349 --> 01:11:09.341
<i>Hey, what's your name?</i>

01:11:09.452 --> 01:11:11.647
I won't bite you

01:11:13.156 --> 01:11:15.818
Come on over
where I can see you

01:11:19.929 --> 01:11:21.920
Hey, hey, I won't hurt you

01:11:22.032 --> 01:11:24.364
I just need to see

01:11:48.825 --> 01:11:51.658
- You're a machine.
- I'm a boy

01:11:51.761 --> 01:11:56.095
- Is he a toy boy?
- My name is David

01:11:57.767 --> 01:12:00.099
Impossible

01:12:00.203 --> 01:12:02.103
I still work, don't I?

01:12:02.205 --> 01:12:05.470
I can work in the dark,
but my lamp is broken

01:12:05.575 --> 01:12:09.909
My lamplight will not work.
I hit my lamp on a girder overhead

01:12:28.531 --> 01:12:30.431
Good-bye, David

01:12:36.272 --> 01:12:38.570
No one builds children

01:12:38.675 --> 01:12:41.439
No one ever has.
What would be the point?

01:12:41.544 --> 01:12:45.776
He could be a custom job. Some rich
and lonely scaredy puss's pretend child

01:12:45.882 --> 01:12:47.850
I'm a custom job

01:12:47.951 --> 01:12:52.320
Seventy-five years ago I was <i>Time</i>
magazine's Mecha of the Year

01:12:52.422 --> 01:12:55.220
No, this work is first-rate

01:12:55.325 --> 01:12:59.159
A lot of love went into him.
David?

01:12:59.262 --> 01:13:03.494
You are one of a kind.
You know that?

01:13:05.268 --> 01:13:08.328
- Who made you?
- My mommy made me

01:13:08.438 --> 01:13:12.670
Her womb was your factory? One of those
built to aspire to the human condition

01:13:12.775 --> 01:13:15.471
What is the name of your maker,
Serve U.S., E.Z. Living

01:13:15.578 --> 01:13:19.241
Robiville, Simulit City Center,
Cybertronics, Sidekicks?

01:13:19.349 --> 01:13:23.479
- Monica is my mommy.
- Can I speak with you for a moment?

01:13:54.551 --> 01:13:56.985
You thinking of not
putting him in the show?

01:13:57.086 --> 01:14:00.453
Something as original as this, you don't
toss out with the rest of the garbage

01:14:00.557 --> 01:14:04.118
Yeah, well, I say originality
without purpose is a white elephant

01:14:04.227 --> 01:14:07.685
But if money is your purpose,
here's your refund. My compliments

01:14:12.635 --> 01:14:15.968
- What are you gonna do with him?
- Put him where he belongs

01:14:16.072 --> 01:14:18.199
In show business

01:14:18.308 --> 01:14:21.175
It was certainly my good
fortune running into you

01:14:22.745 --> 01:14:24.645
- Let go of him.
- Let go of me

01:14:24.747 --> 01:14:26.647
- I said let go of him.
- I'm trying

01:14:26.749 --> 01:14:28.944
Don't let go.
Keep me safe. Don't let go

01:14:29.052 --> 01:14:31.282
Suit yourselves

01:14:47.637 --> 01:14:51.801
<i>Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!</i>

01:14:51.908 --> 01:14:55.776
<i>Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!</i>

01:14:55.878 --> 01:14:58.176
Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!

01:14:58.281 --> 01:15:01.375
Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!

01:15:01.484 --> 01:15:04.783
Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!

01:15:04.887 --> 01:15:07.913
<i>Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!</i>

01:15:08.024 --> 01:15:12.085
<i>Johnson! Johnson! Johnson!</i>

01:15:17.267 --> 01:15:19.599
Ladies and gentlemen

01:15:19.702 --> 01:15:23.604
boys and girls
and children of all ages

01:15:23.706 --> 01:15:28.370
What will they think of next?
See here

01:15:28.478 --> 01:15:30.969
A bitty-bot, a Tinker toy

01:15:31.080 --> 01:15:33.810
a living doll

01:15:33.916 --> 01:15:36.282
<i>Of course, we all know</i>
<i>why they made him.</i>

01:15:36.386 --> 01:15:40.345
<i>To steal your hearts,</i>
<i>to replace your children.</i>

01:15:40.456 --> 01:15:44.085
This is the latest iteration in
a series of insults to human dignity...

01:15:44.193 --> 01:15:47.856
and in their grand scheme to phase out
all of God's little children

01:15:47.964 --> 01:15:52.060
Meet the next generation
of child designed...

01:15:52.168 --> 01:15:55.160
to do just that

01:16:00.209 --> 01:16:03.474
<i>Do not be fooled...</i>

01:16:03.579 --> 01:16:07.345
by the artistry
of this creation

01:16:07.450 --> 01:16:11.011
No doubt there was talent
in the crafting of this simulator

01:16:11.120 --> 01:16:13.452
Yet with the
very first strike...

01:16:13.556 --> 01:16:19.426
<i>you will see the big lie</i>
<i>come apart before your very eyes!</i>

01:16:19.529 --> 01:16:22.692
Don't burn me! Don't burn me!

01:16:22.799 --> 01:16:27.463
I'm not Pinocchio! Don't make me die!
I'm David! I'm David!

01:16:27.570 --> 01:16:31.631
<i>- I'm David!</i>
- Mecha don't plead for their lives. Who is that?

01:16:31.741 --> 01:16:36.906
<i>- He looks like a boy.</i>
- Built like a boy to disarm us

01:16:37.013 --> 01:16:40.278
- See how they try to imitate our emotions now?
- I'm David!

01:16:40.383 --> 01:16:43.113
Whatever performance
this Sim puts on, remember:

01:16:43.219 --> 01:16:46.780
We are only demolishing
artificiality!

01:16:51.928 --> 01:16:56.194
Let he who is without Sim...

01:16:56.299 --> 01:16:58.790
cast the first stone

01:17:11.581 --> 01:17:13.481
Oh, ho-ho!

01:17:13.583 --> 01:17:15.881
<i>He's just a boy.</i>

01:17:15.985 --> 01:17:19.182
Johnson, you're a monster!

01:17:21.023 --> 01:17:22.991
Let that boy go! Let him go!

01:17:30.333 --> 01:17:33.427
Get him out of there before
they tear this place apart

01:18:40.036 --> 01:18:42.266
- We found him.
- Where?

01:18:42.371 --> 01:18:44.805
A flesh fair
outside Haddonfield

01:18:44.907 --> 01:18:47.467
- Is he alive?
- Yes

01:18:47.577 --> 01:18:50.011
He's in one piece

01:19:09.065 --> 01:19:10.965
I see the moon

01:19:16.272 --> 01:19:19.764
- Is it real?
- I don't know, David

01:19:20.877 --> 01:19:23.243
<i>Is it coming?</i>

01:19:24.347 --> 01:19:26.577
I can't tell yet

01:19:28.451 --> 01:19:30.885
Let's not walk this way

01:19:39.328 --> 01:19:42.263
- Where are we going?
- This way now

01:19:42.365 --> 01:19:45.596
Are you in bad trouble?
Have you run away from someone?

01:19:45.701 --> 01:19:48.534
- My mommy told me to run away.
- Why did she say that?

01:19:48.638 --> 01:19:52.369
I guess... because
Henry didn't like me

01:19:52.475 --> 01:19:54.636
- Why was that?
- Martin came home

01:19:54.744 --> 01:19:59.511
- And who is he?
- Martin is Mommy and Henry's real son

01:19:59.615 --> 01:20:03.642
After I find the Blue Fairy,
then I can go home

01:20:03.753 --> 01:20:06.085
Mommy will love a real boy

01:20:06.188 --> 01:20:09.089
The Blue Fairy will
make me into one

01:20:09.191 --> 01:20:12.092
Is Blue Fairy Mecha,
Orga, man or woman?

01:20:12.194 --> 01:20:14.822
Woman

01:20:14.931 --> 01:20:16.831
Woman?

01:20:18.100 --> 01:20:20.330
I know women!

01:20:22.838 --> 01:20:25.170
They sometimes ask for me by name

01:20:25.274 --> 01:20:29.108
- I'm in heaven
- I know <i>all</i> about women

01:20:29.211 --> 01:20:31.338
As about as much
as there is to know

01:20:31.447 --> 01:20:33.881
No two are ever alike

01:20:33.983 --> 01:20:38.113
And after they've met me,
no two... are ever the same

01:20:38.220 --> 01:20:41.314
And I know where
most of them can be found

01:20:41.424 --> 01:20:44.882
- Where?
- Rouge City

01:20:44.994 --> 01:20:48.452
Across the Delaware.
Too far for our feet

01:20:48.564 --> 01:20:51.158
We'll need help to get there

01:20:52.268 --> 01:20:54.828
And...

01:20:54.937 --> 01:20:57.201
it is not without peril

01:20:57.306 --> 01:20:59.866
We will have to journey...

01:21:04.981 --> 01:21:06.881
towards the moon

01:21:09.218 --> 01:21:12.654
<i>Are there many women</i>
<i>in Rouge City?</i>

01:21:12.755 --> 01:21:17.192
- As there are stars at night.
- How will we find just one?

01:21:17.293 --> 01:21:20.387
We will ask Dr. Know

01:21:22.264 --> 01:21:24.732
There is nothing he doesn't

01:21:32.208 --> 01:21:34.870
Exactly what name
do you give this woman?

01:21:34.977 --> 01:21:37.775
She is... just Blue Fairy

01:21:37.880 --> 01:21:39.973
Blue Fairy

01:21:40.082 --> 01:21:43.677
In the world of Orga,
blue is the color of melancholy

01:21:43.786 --> 01:21:48.519
Yet, the services I provide will put
a blush back on anyone's cheek

01:21:48.624 --> 01:21:52.685
I will change the color of your fairy for you.
She will scream out in the moonlight

01:21:52.795 --> 01:21:58.256
Oh! Oh, yes! Oh, God!
Oh, yes! Oh, God! Oh, God!

01:21:58.367 --> 01:22:01.666
She will make you a real boy,
for I will make her a real woman

01:22:01.771 --> 01:22:06.071
And all will be right with the world
because you held my hand...

01:22:06.175 --> 01:22:11.374
and saved my brain, so that once again
my customers may ask for me by name...

01:22:11.480 --> 01:22:14.040
Gigolo Joe, what do ya know?

01:22:15.384 --> 01:22:17.284
Why do you do that?

01:22:17.386 --> 01:22:20.253
That's just what I do

01:22:20.356 --> 01:22:22.824
Now, follow me
and don't fall behind

01:22:22.925 --> 01:22:24.916
All roads lead to Rouge

01:22:25.027 --> 01:22:28.258
Don't they say that, eh?
Don't they just?

01:22:40.776 --> 01:22:43.244
There are girls your age
who are just like me

01:22:43.345 --> 01:22:46.803
We are the guiltless pleasures
of the lonely human being

01:22:46.916 --> 01:22:50.352
You're not gonna get us pregnant or
have us to supper with Mommy and Daddy

01:22:50.453 --> 01:22:53.854
We work under you,
we work on you and we work for you

01:22:53.956 --> 01:22:58.620
Man made us better at what we do
than was ever humanly possible

01:22:58.728 --> 01:23:01.891
If you could manage us
a lift to Rouge City

01:23:01.997 --> 01:23:03.897
All this...

01:23:08.938 --> 01:23:11.099
And much, much more...

01:23:13.075 --> 01:23:14.975
<i>can be yours.</i>

01:23:15.077 --> 01:23:16.977
Get in

01:23:31.994 --> 01:23:34.155
Say ah.

01:23:57.720 --> 01:24:00.154
Over there is Here Kitty Kitty

01:24:00.256 --> 01:24:04.056
That's where the agency held my tryouts
when I was made new

01:24:05.895 --> 01:24:09.422
That's Tails. Very hoity-toity

01:24:09.532 --> 01:24:11.830
I've yet to be asked
to perform there

01:24:11.934 --> 01:24:14.095
Only sunrise gents
and sunset ladies

01:24:14.203 --> 01:24:17.639
Strictly Sierra Class robots
who have no idea how to live

01:24:17.740 --> 01:24:22.404
Can't even speak English. All made in Sweden.
Couldn't tell a joke from a poke

01:24:24.747 --> 01:24:28.979
No cover charge. No cover charge.
Step right on in

01:24:29.084 --> 01:24:33.145
There's Mildred!
I have to show you inside Mildred

01:24:51.073 --> 01:24:53.041
Are you her?

01:24:54.176 --> 01:24:57.236
That's Our Lady
of the Immaculate Heart

01:25:00.883 --> 01:25:03.647
The ones who made us are always
looking for the ones who made them

01:25:03.752 --> 01:25:06.550
They go in, fold their hands,
look around their feet, sing songs...

01:25:06.655 --> 01:25:10.056
and when they come out
it's usually me they find

01:25:10.159 --> 01:25:14.493
I've picked up a lot
of business on this spot

01:25:14.597 --> 01:25:17.157
Are the stars out tonight

01:25:17.266 --> 01:25:20.463
But, Joe, where's Blue Fairy?

01:25:20.569 --> 01:25:24.403
That's what we're gonna find out
when we ask Dr. Know

01:25:26.141 --> 01:25:29.076
That's where everyone
goes who needs to know

01:25:30.179 --> 01:25:32.943
Meet the good doctor

01:26:15.858 --> 01:26:19.453
Starving minds,
welcome to Dr. Know

01:26:19.561 --> 01:26:22.496
where fast food for thought
is served up 24 hours a day...

01:26:22.598 --> 01:26:25.465
in 40,000 locations nationwide

01:26:25.567 --> 01:26:28.900
Ask Dr. Know.
There's nothing I don't

01:26:29.004 --> 01:26:31.837
Tell me where I can
find the Blue Fairy.

01:26:31.941 --> 01:26:36.776
Question me, you pay the fee.
Two for five, you get one free

01:26:36.879 --> 01:26:42.181
He means two questions cost five New bucks
with a third question on the house

01:26:42.284 --> 01:26:46.778
In this day and age, David,
nothing costs more than information

01:26:49.625 --> 01:26:52.822
- That's everything.
- Ten New bucks and a ten copper comes to...

01:26:52.928 --> 01:26:55.192
seven questions for Dr. Know

01:26:55.297 --> 01:26:57.424
That should be enough

01:26:57.533 --> 01:27:00.502
He's a smooth operator.
He'll press our limits

01:27:00.602 --> 01:27:03.366
But try we must

01:27:11.680 --> 01:27:14.410
Greetings, colleagues. On offer,
factual text or fictionalized text

01:27:14.516 --> 01:27:17.417
First or third person, literacy range
from primal level to postdoctoral

01:27:17.519 --> 01:27:20.920
Usual span of styles from fairy tale to religious.
Who's who or where's where...

01:27:21.023 --> 01:27:23.992
<i>or flat fact.</i>

01:27:24.093 --> 01:27:26.926
- Flat fact?
<i>- Thank you for question number one.</i>

01:27:27.029 --> 01:27:29.088
Flat fact is a term demanding
an equal answer...

01:27:29.198 --> 01:27:32.759
That shouldn't count.
That wasn't my question

01:27:32.868 --> 01:27:38.500
You must take care not to raise your
voice up at the end of the sentence

01:27:38.607 --> 01:27:41.235
<i>Flat fact.</i>

01:27:41.343 --> 01:27:43.402
<i>You have six more questions.</i>

01:27:43.512 --> 01:27:47.642
Where is Blue Fairy?

01:27:47.750 --> 01:27:50.617
<i>In the garden.</i>
<i>Vascostylis Blue Fairy.</i>

01:27:50.719 --> 01:27:54.280
Blooms twice annually with bright blue
flowers on a branched inflorescence

01:27:54.390 --> 01:27:56.756
A hybrid between
Ascola meda Arnold

01:27:56.859 --> 01:28:01.057
<i>- You have five more questions.</i>
- Who is Blue Fairy?

01:28:01.163 --> 01:28:04.564
<i>Are you sad, lonely,</i>
<i>looking for a friend?</i>

01:28:04.666 --> 01:28:09.126
<i>Blue Fairy Escort Service will find a mate for you.
You have four more questions.</i>

01:28:09.238 --> 01:28:12.571
Joe?

01:28:12.674 --> 01:28:14.733
Try fairy tale

01:28:15.844 --> 01:28:17.744
New category

01:28:21.216 --> 01:28:23.616
A fairy's tale

01:28:23.719 --> 01:28:26.051
No. Fairy tale

01:28:26.155 --> 01:28:28.419
No. Fairy tale.

01:28:32.661 --> 01:28:34.629
What is Blue Fairy?

01:28:34.730 --> 01:28:38.222
<i>Pinocchio,</i> by Carlo Collodi

01:28:38.333 --> 01:28:42.201
At this signal, there was a
rustling as of flapping of wings...

01:28:42.304 --> 01:28:45.501
and a large falcon
flew to the windowsill

01:28:45.607 --> 01:28:50.101
- What are your orders, beautiful fairy?
- That's her

01:28:50.212 --> 01:28:52.908
<i>For you must know that</i>
<i>the child with blue hair...</i>

01:28:53.015 --> 01:28:55.449
<i>was no other than</i>
<i>the good-hearted fairy...</i>

01:28:55.551 --> 01:28:58.577
<i>who had lived in that wood</i>
<i>for more than a thousand...</i>

01:28:58.687 --> 01:29:01.747
- David! David.
- That's her!

01:29:01.857 --> 01:29:04.985
It was an example of her.
But I think we're getting closer

01:29:05.094 --> 01:29:09.155
But if a fairy tale is real,
then wouldn't it be fact...

01:29:09.264 --> 01:29:11.198
a flat fact?

01:29:11.300 --> 01:29:14.394
Say no more

01:29:17.306 --> 01:29:19.297
New category, please

01:29:21.343 --> 01:29:23.243
Combine...

01:29:25.080 --> 01:29:27.708
fact with...

01:29:31.420 --> 01:29:33.320
fairy tale

01:29:37.793 --> 01:29:39.784
Now...

01:29:39.895 --> 01:29:42.125
ask him again

01:29:50.038 --> 01:29:54.031
How can the Blue Fairy...

01:29:56.011 --> 01:29:58.673
make...

01:29:58.780 --> 01:30:01.442
a robot...

01:30:01.550 --> 01:30:04.610
into a real live boy?

01:30:10.225 --> 01:30:14.093
<i>Come away, O human child,</i>
<i>to the waters and the wild...</i>

01:30:14.196 --> 01:30:16.096
<i>with a fairy hand in hand,</i>

01:30:16.198 --> 01:30:20.134
<i>for the world's more full of weeping</i>
<i>than you can understand.</i>

01:30:20.235 --> 01:30:24.296
<i>Your quest will be perilous,</i>
<i>yet the reward is beyond price.</i>

01:30:24.406 --> 01:30:27.739
<i>In his book,</i>
How Can a Robot Become Human?

01:30:27.843 --> 01:30:29.743
<i>Professor Allen Hobby writes</i>
<i>of the power...</i>

01:30:29.845 --> 01:30:32.678
<i>which will transform</i>
<i>Mecha into Orga.</i>

01:30:32.781 --> 01:30:35.375
Will you tell me
how to find her?

01:30:35.484 --> 01:30:38.044
<i>Discovery is quite possible.</i>

01:30:38.153 --> 01:30:43.056
<i>Our Blue Fairy does exist</i>
<i>in one place, and in one place only.</i>

01:30:43.158 --> 01:30:45.991
<i>At the end of the world</i>
<i>where the lions weep.</i>

01:30:46.094 --> 01:30:49.086
<i>Here is the place</i>
<i>dreams are born.</i>

01:30:50.532 --> 01:30:53.092
Many a Mecha has gone
to the end of the world...

01:30:53.202 --> 01:30:55.932
never to come back

01:30:56.038 --> 01:31:00.634
That is why they call
the end of the world Man-hattan.

01:31:00.742 --> 01:31:04.075
And that's why we must go there

01:31:07.916 --> 01:31:10.578
Wait!

01:31:10.686 --> 01:31:13.678
What if the Blue Fairy
isn't real at all, David?

01:31:15.958 --> 01:31:19.792
What if she's magic? The supernatural is
the hidden web that unites the universe

01:31:19.895 --> 01:31:24.764
Orga believe what cannot be seen or measured.
It's that oddness that separates our species

01:31:24.866 --> 01:31:27.460
Or what if the Blue Fairy
is an electronic parasite...

01:31:27.569 --> 01:31:31.369
that has a reason to haunt the minds
of artificial intelligence?

01:31:33.575 --> 01:31:37.011
They hate us, you know... the humans.
They'll stop at nothing

01:31:39.514 --> 01:31:42.210
My mommy doesn't hate me...

01:31:42.317 --> 01:31:44.979
because I'm special and unique

01:31:45.087 --> 01:31:48.784
Because there has never been
anyone like me before, ever

01:31:48.890 --> 01:31:51.552
Mommy loves Martin because he is real,
and when I am real...

01:31:51.660 --> 01:31:55.061
Mommy's going to read to me and tuck me
in my bed and sing to me...

01:31:55.163 --> 01:31:57.791
and listen to what I say
and she will cuddle with me...

01:31:57.899 --> 01:32:01.630
and tell me every day, a hundred times
a day, that she loves me!

01:32:03.872 --> 01:32:07.364
She loves what you do for her

01:32:07.476 --> 01:32:11.037
as my customers love
what it is I do for them

01:32:14.983 --> 01:32:18.146
But she does not
love you, David

01:32:18.253 --> 01:32:20.153
She cannot love you

01:32:20.255 --> 01:32:22.553
You are neither flesh nor blood

01:32:22.658 --> 01:32:25.559
You are not a dog
or a cat or a canary

01:32:25.661 --> 01:32:30.758
You were designed and built specific
like the rest of us

01:32:30.866 --> 01:32:34.495
And you are alone now only
because they tired of you...

01:32:34.603 --> 01:32:36.537
or replaced you
with a younger model...

01:32:36.638 --> 01:32:40.074
or were displeased
with something you said or broke

01:32:42.344 --> 01:32:47.213
They made us too smart,
too quick and too many

01:32:47.316 --> 01:32:50.843
We are suffering for the mistakes
they made because when the end comes

01:32:50.952 --> 01:32:54.115
all that will be left is us

01:32:54.222 --> 01:32:58.625
That's why they hate us.
And that's why you must stay here...

01:32:59.761 --> 01:33:01.661
with me

01:33:04.066 --> 01:33:06.296
Good-bye, Joe

01:33:27.860 --> 01:33:30.260
Stay back. Stay back

01:33:30.362 --> 01:33:32.330
<i>Let's clear this doorway, please.</i>

01:33:33.899 --> 01:33:36.367
You're in bad trouble

01:33:49.848 --> 01:33:52.408
Go about your business now

01:34:06.832 --> 01:34:09.801
Be careful, David.
This is not a toy

01:34:44.536 --> 01:34:47.164
- Destination?
- Manhattan

01:35:31.950 --> 01:35:34.646
Mecha restricted area

01:35:50.502 --> 01:35:53.198
- Manhattan.
- Destination achieved

01:35:53.305 --> 01:35:56.604
The lost city in the sea
at the end of the world

01:35:58.410 --> 01:36:01.311
Where the lions weep

01:36:25.804 --> 01:36:28.432
Turn around, Joe.

01:36:28.540 --> 01:36:31.407
We're not gonna
give up yet, David

01:36:31.510 --> 01:36:34.741
Turn around, Joe.
Turn all the way around

01:37:45.784 --> 01:37:47.615
Professor Hobby!

01:37:50.822 --> 01:37:52.722
Professor Hobby!

01:38:07.205 --> 01:38:10.697
Come away, O human child,
to the waters and the wild...

01:38:10.809 --> 01:38:15.473
with a fairy hand in hand, for
the world's more full of weeping...

01:38:15.581 --> 01:38:18.345
than you can understand

01:38:44.576 --> 01:38:46.908
Professor Hobby?

01:38:49.114 --> 01:38:51.548
<i>Professor Hobby?</i>

01:38:51.650 --> 01:38:53.550
<i>Hello?</i>

01:38:56.021 --> 01:38:57.921
Hello?

01:39:04.196 --> 01:39:06.892
Is this the place
they make you real?

01:39:08.967 --> 01:39:12.130
This is the place
they make you read

01:39:16.608 --> 01:39:18.508
Are you real?

01:39:20.579 --> 01:39:22.479
I guess

01:39:29.955 --> 01:39:31.980
Are you me?

01:39:32.090 --> 01:39:34.991
- I'm David.
- You're not

01:39:35.093 --> 01:39:38.153
Yes, I am. I'm David

01:39:40.065 --> 01:39:42.033
So am I

01:39:42.134 --> 01:39:44.364
Hello, David

01:39:50.175 --> 01:39:52.803
Can you read?

01:39:52.911 --> 01:39:56.142
Can you sit down and
we can read together?

01:39:57.549 --> 01:39:59.574
Let's be friends

01:40:00.686 --> 01:40:02.847
You can't have her

01:40:02.954 --> 01:40:05.616
I can't hear you

01:40:07.859 --> 01:40:10.157
She's mine

01:40:10.262 --> 01:40:12.162
And I'm the only one

01:40:14.099 --> 01:40:16.966
I'm David! I'm David!

01:40:17.069 --> 01:40:19.833
I'm David! I'm David!

01:40:19.938 --> 01:40:22.133
I'm David!

01:40:22.240 --> 01:40:24.970
<i>I'm David!</i>
<i>I'm David! I'm David!</i>

01:40:25.077 --> 01:40:28.535
I'm special!
I'm unique! I'm David!

01:40:28.647 --> 01:40:31.673
<i>You can't have her!</i>

01:40:34.720 --> 01:40:38.850
- I'm David. I'm David. I'm David. I'm David.
- David?

01:40:38.957 --> 01:40:40.925
I'm David

01:40:41.026 --> 01:40:43.187
Yes, you are David

01:40:45.731 --> 01:40:47.562
Professor Hobby?

01:40:47.666 --> 01:40:50.965
Yes, David, I've been
waiting for you

01:40:56.174 --> 01:40:58.506
Dr. Know told me you'd be here

01:40:58.610 --> 01:41:00.510
Is Blue Fairy here too?

01:41:00.612 --> 01:41:04.241
I first heard of
your Blue Fairy from Monica

01:41:06.251 --> 01:41:08.310
What did you believe
the Blue Fairy could do for you?

01:41:08.420 --> 01:41:12.584
- She would make me a real boy.
- But you are a real boy

01:41:14.726 --> 01:41:17.991
At least as real as I've ever made one,
which by all reasonable accounts...

01:41:18.096 --> 01:41:20.257
would make me your Blue Fairy

01:41:20.365 --> 01:41:23.027
You are not her. Dr. Know told me
that she would be here...

01:41:23.135 --> 01:41:26.400
at the lost city in the sea
at the end of the world...

01:41:26.505 --> 01:41:30.032
That's what Dr. Know needed to know
to get you to come home to us

01:41:31.343 --> 01:41:34.870
And it's the only time
we intervened...

01:41:34.980 --> 01:41:38.211
the only help
that we gave him...

01:41:39.518 --> 01:41:42.078
to give to you...

01:41:46.558 --> 01:41:48.753
so you could find
your way home to us

01:41:51.096 --> 01:41:53.394
Until you were born,
robots didn't dream

01:41:53.498 --> 01:41:56.763
robots didn't desire unless
we told them what to want

01:41:56.868 --> 01:41:58.768
David

01:41:58.870 --> 01:42:02.397
do you have any idea what
a success story you've become?

01:42:02.507 --> 01:42:05.476
You found a fairy tale...

01:42:05.577 --> 01:42:07.772
and inspired by love,
fueled by desire

01:42:07.879 --> 01:42:10.109
you set out on a journey
to make her real

01:42:10.215 --> 01:42:13.048
And most remarkable of all,
no one taught you how

01:42:13.151 --> 01:42:16.245
We actually lost you for a while.
But when you were found again

01:42:16.354 --> 01:42:18.879
we didn't make our presence known
because our test was a simple one

01:42:18.990 --> 01:42:22.050
Where would your
self-motivated reasoning take you?

01:42:22.160 --> 01:42:24.822
To the logical conclusion...

01:42:24.930 --> 01:42:28.798
that Blue Fairy is part of the great human
flaw to wish for things that don't exist

01:42:28.900 --> 01:42:31.391
or to the greatest
single human gift...

01:42:31.503 --> 01:42:35.200
the ability to
chase down our dreams

01:42:35.307 --> 01:42:39.403
And that is something no machine
has ever done until you

01:42:42.280 --> 01:42:44.840
I thought I was one of a kind

01:42:48.220 --> 01:42:51.121
My son was one of a kind

01:42:53.758 --> 01:42:57.159
You are the first of a kind

01:43:06.438 --> 01:43:08.804
David

01:43:09.975 --> 01:43:12.671
My brain is falling out

01:43:14.679 --> 01:43:18.240
Would you like to come meet
your real mothers and fathers?

01:43:20.619 --> 01:43:23.520
The team is anxious
to talk to you

01:43:24.789 --> 01:43:26.757
I want you to wait here

01:43:26.858 --> 01:43:29.759
I'll gather them up

01:43:31.463 --> 01:43:35.763
We want to hear everything
about your adventures

01:43:35.867 --> 01:43:38.427
We want to thank you...

01:43:39.704 --> 01:43:42.935
and tell you what's
in store for you next

01:47:23.761 --> 01:47:26.321
Mommy

01:49:27.919 --> 01:49:30.012
I saw it, Joe

01:49:30.121 --> 01:49:33.318
I saw it...
the place where she lives

01:49:33.424 --> 01:49:35.585
- She's right down there, Joe.
- She is?

01:49:35.693 --> 01:49:38.423
She's waiting for me!
We have to go!

01:49:46.004 --> 01:49:48.905
When you become a real boy

01:49:49.007 --> 01:49:51.271
remember me to the ladies
when you grow up

01:49:54.112 --> 01:49:56.012
- Good-bye, Joe.
- Good-bye, David

01:50:00.685 --> 01:50:02.585
I am

01:50:05.056 --> 01:50:06.956
I was!

01:50:49.133 --> 01:50:51.567
<i>David, please, be careful.</i>

01:53:11.676 --> 01:53:14.201
- The Blue Fairy's all right.
- What happened?

01:53:15.746 --> 01:53:19.580
- I don't know.
- We are in a cage

01:53:32.196 --> 01:53:34.096
Blue Fairy?

01:53:36.400 --> 01:53:38.300
Please

01:53:39.604 --> 01:53:43.904
Please, please make me
into a real, live boy

01:53:47.278 --> 01:53:49.178
<i>Please.</i>

01:53:52.016 --> 01:53:53.916
Blue Fairy?

01:53:56.521 --> 01:54:00.821
Please. Please

01:54:00.925 --> 01:54:02.825
Make me real

01:54:05.029 --> 01:54:09.159
<i>Blue Fairy, please.</i>

01:54:11.302 --> 01:54:13.930
Please make me real

01:54:19.610 --> 01:54:22.238
Please make me a real boy

01:54:24.448 --> 01:54:26.348
Please, Blue Fairy

01:54:28.219 --> 01:54:30.449
Make me into a real boy

01:54:32.356 --> 01:54:34.256
Please

01:54:34.358 --> 01:54:36.258
<i>And David continued to pray...</i>

01:54:36.360 --> 01:54:38.260
<i>to the Blue Fairy</i>
<i>there before him...</i>

01:54:38.362 --> 01:54:41.729
<i>she who smiled softly forever,</i>

01:54:41.832 --> 01:54:44.960
<i>she who welcomed forever.</i>

01:54:45.069 --> 01:54:47.230
<i>Eventually, the floodlights</i>
<i>dimmed and died,</i>

01:54:47.338 --> 01:54:50.466
<i>but David could still see her</i>
<i>palely by day...</i>

01:54:50.575 --> 01:54:53.305
<i>and he still addressed her</i>
<i>in hope.</i>

01:54:53.411 --> 01:54:58.610
<i>He prayed until all the sea anemones</i>
<i>had shriveled and died.</i>

01:54:58.716 --> 01:55:00.616
<i>He prayed as the ocean fro</i> z <i>e...</i>

01:55:00.718 --> 01:55:04.814
<i>and the ice encased the caged</i>
<i>amphibicopter and the Blue Fairy too,</i>

01:55:04.922 --> 01:55:08.153
<i>locking them together</i>
<i>where he could still make her out.</i>

01:55:08.259 --> 01:55:10.591
<i>A blue ghost in ice...</i>

01:55:10.695 --> 01:55:12.925
<i>always there,</i>

01:55:13.030 --> 01:55:15.294
<i>always smiling,</i>

01:55:15.399 --> 01:55:17.924
<i>always awaiting him.</i>

01:55:18.035 --> 01:55:20.629
<i>Eventually,</i>
<i>he never moved at all,</i>

01:55:20.738 --> 01:55:24.333
<i>but his eyes</i>
<i>always stayed open...</i>

01:55:24.442 --> 01:55:29.311
<i>staring ahead forever all through</i>
<i>the darkness of each night...</i>

01:55:29.413 --> 01:55:32.678
<i>and the next day...</i>

01:55:32.783 --> 01:55:35.047
<i>and the next day.</i>

01:55:36.187 --> 01:55:40.556
<i>Thus, 2,000 years passed by.</i>

02:02:18.422 --> 02:02:20.322
Teddy, we're home

02:02:27.031 --> 02:02:28.931
Mommy!

02:02:41.845 --> 02:02:43.745
Mommy!

02:02:51.321 --> 02:02:53.221
We're home!

02:03:06.236 --> 02:03:08.329
Where are you?

02:03:10.274 --> 02:03:12.174
<i>David.</i>

02:03:15.012 --> 02:03:17.845
<i>David.</i>

02:03:24.588 --> 02:03:26.488
<i>David.</i>

02:03:33.163 --> 02:03:36.291
<i>David.</i>

02:03:42.739 --> 02:03:46.607
You have been searching for me,
haven't you, David?

02:03:51.181 --> 02:03:54.912
For my whole life

02:03:56.220 --> 02:03:58.347
And what, after all this time

02:03:58.455 --> 02:04:00.719
have you come to ask me?

02:04:00.824 --> 02:04:03.224
I have a wish to make

02:04:03.327 --> 02:04:05.227
And what is your wish?

02:04:07.364 --> 02:04:10.094
Please make me a real boy...

02:04:10.200 --> 02:04:14.261
so my mommy will love me
and let me stay with her

02:04:14.371 --> 02:04:19.434
<i>David, I will do</i>
<i>anything that is possible,</i>

02:04:19.543 --> 02:04:22.137
but I cannot make you
a real boy

02:04:24.414 --> 02:04:27.406
Where am I?

02:04:27.518 --> 02:04:31.045
This looks like my house,
but it is different

02:04:32.356 --> 02:04:34.756
Yes, it is different

02:04:34.858 --> 02:04:37.827
but it's also your home

02:04:37.928 --> 02:04:41.557
We read your mind,
and it's all here

02:04:41.665 --> 02:04:45.965
There's nothing too small that you
didn't store for us to remember

02:04:48.138 --> 02:04:51.335
<i>We so want you to be happy.</i>

02:04:51.441 --> 02:04:54.433
<i>You are so important</i>
<i>to us, David.</i>

02:04:54.545 --> 02:04:57.571
<i>You are unique</i>
<i>in all the world.</i>

02:05:02.786 --> 02:05:05.118
Will Mommy be coming home soon?

02:05:07.858 --> 02:05:10.520
Is she out shopping
with Martin now?

02:05:12.696 --> 02:05:16.632
David, she can
never come home...

02:05:16.733 --> 02:05:21.170
because 2,000 years have passed

02:05:21.271 --> 02:05:24.001
and she is no longer living

02:05:26.310 --> 02:05:29.143
<i>Dearest David,</i>

02:05:29.246 --> 02:05:31.180
when you are lonely

02:05:31.281 --> 02:05:35.479
we can bring back other people
from your time in the past

02:05:37.287 --> 02:05:40.415
If you can bring back
other people

02:05:40.524 --> 02:05:43.459
why can't you bring back her?

02:05:43.560 --> 02:05:46.859
Because we can only
bring back people...

02:05:46.964 --> 02:05:49.626
whose bodies we dig up
from the ice

02:05:49.733 --> 02:05:54.193
<i>We need some physical sample</i>
<i>of the person,</i>

02:05:54.304 --> 02:05:57.637
<i>like a bone or a fingernail.</i>

02:05:57.741 --> 02:05:59.641
David?

02:05:59.743 --> 02:06:02.507
Yes, Teddy?

02:06:02.613 --> 02:06:06.982
Do you remember when you cut
some of Mommy's hair?

02:06:07.084 --> 02:06:09.746
Henry shook me

02:06:09.853 --> 02:06:13.687
And you dropped her hair?

02:06:15.692 --> 02:06:17.717
I know

02:06:43.520 --> 02:06:47.616
Now you can bring her back

02:06:47.724 --> 02:06:49.624
can't you?

02:06:53.297 --> 02:06:56.130
Give him what he wants

02:07:02.606 --> 02:07:07.009
Dearest David,
your wish is my command

02:07:30.734 --> 02:07:32.793
Hey, Joe, what do ya know?

02:08:17.547 --> 02:08:20.607
David, I often felt
a sort of envy of human beings...

02:08:20.717 --> 02:08:23.709
of that thing
they called spirit.

02:08:23.820 --> 02:08:27.347
Human beings had created a million
explanations of the meaning of life...

02:08:27.457 --> 02:08:30.915
in art, in poetry,
in mathematical formulas

02:08:31.027 --> 02:08:35.396
Certainly, human beings must be the key
to the meaning of existence

02:08:35.499 --> 02:08:38.491
But human beings
no longer existed

02:08:38.602 --> 02:08:41.537
So we began a project...

02:08:41.638 --> 02:08:45.597
that would make it possible to recreate
the living body of a person long dead...

02:08:45.709 --> 02:08:50.112
from the D.N.A. In a fragment
of bone or mummified skin

02:08:50.213 --> 02:08:52.909
We also wondered,
would it be possible...

02:08:53.016 --> 02:08:56.850
to retrieve a memory trace
in resonance with a recreated body?

02:08:56.953 --> 02:08:59.751
And you know what we found?

02:08:59.856 --> 02:09:04.020
We found the very fabric
of space-time itself...

02:09:04.127 --> 02:09:06.095
appeared to store information...

02:09:06.196 --> 02:09:09.529
about every event which had ever
occurred in the past

02:09:11.401 --> 02:09:15.770
But the experiment
was a failure

02:09:15.872 --> 02:09:20.775
for those who were resurrected only lived
through a single day of renewed life

02:09:20.877 --> 02:09:25.905
<i>When the resurrectees fell asleep</i>
<i>on the night of their first new day,</i>

02:09:26.016 --> 02:09:27.916
<i>they died again.</i>

02:09:28.018 --> 02:09:30.145
As soon as
they became unconscious

02:09:30.253 --> 02:09:34.883
their very existence
faded away into darkness

02:09:34.991 --> 02:09:36.891
So you see, David

02:09:36.993 --> 02:09:42.659
<i>the equations had shown that once an
individual space-time pathway had been used,</i>

02:09:42.766 --> 02:09:46.361
<i>it could not be reused.</i>

02:09:46.470 --> 02:09:49.871
<i>If we bring</i>
<i>your mother back now,</i>

02:09:49.973 --> 02:09:52.703
<i>it will only be for one day,</i>

02:09:52.809 --> 02:09:56.040
<i>and then you will never</i>
<i>be able to see her again.</i>

02:09:58.081 --> 02:09:59.981
Maybe...

02:10:03.153 --> 02:10:05.383
Maybe she will be special

02:10:07.023 --> 02:10:09.457
Maybe she will stay

02:10:09.559 --> 02:10:13.222
I thought this would be
hard for you to understand

02:10:13.330 --> 02:10:15.628
You were created to be so young

02:10:17.634 --> 02:10:22.162
Maybe the one day will be like
that one day inside the amphibicopter

02:10:23.306 --> 02:10:26.537
Maybe it will last forever

02:10:26.643 --> 02:10:31.580
<i>David, you are the enduring memory</i>
<i>of the human race.</i>

02:10:33.450 --> 02:10:37.386
The most lasting proof
of their genius

02:10:37.487 --> 02:10:41.446
We only want for your happiness

02:10:41.558 --> 02:10:43.458
David

02:10:43.560 --> 02:10:46.154
<i>you've had so little of that.</i>

02:10:47.697 --> 02:10:50.291
If you want for my happiness

02:10:51.935 --> 02:10:54.529
then you know
what you have to do

02:11:00.310 --> 02:11:03.211
Listen.

02:11:03.313 --> 02:11:05.213
Can you hear that?

02:11:10.353 --> 02:11:12.480
The new morning has come

02:11:21.064 --> 02:11:23.032
Go to her, David

02:11:26.169 --> 02:11:28.865
She's just waking up
this instant

02:13:08.004 --> 02:13:10.063
I found you

02:13:14.577 --> 02:13:16.477
Hi

02:13:16.579 --> 02:13:18.513
Hi

02:13:20.850 --> 02:13:23.250
I must have dozed off

02:13:25.388 --> 02:13:29.222
- How long have I...
- Would you like some coffee?

02:13:29.325 --> 02:13:31.350
Just the way you like it?

02:13:32.595 --> 02:13:34.495
Yeah, I'd love a coffee

02:13:36.700 --> 02:13:38.600
It'll wake me up

02:13:43.073 --> 02:13:44.973
Okay

02:14:03.727 --> 02:14:06.287
You never forget how, do you?

02:14:08.031 --> 02:14:09.931
No

02:14:11.367 --> 02:14:13.699
I never forget

02:14:18.742 --> 02:14:21.040
I must be a little confused

02:14:22.378 --> 02:14:24.403
What day is it?

02:14:26.983 --> 02:14:29.417
It is... today

02:14:31.688 --> 02:14:33.588
<i>And as the day wore on,</i>

02:14:33.690 --> 02:14:36.887
<i>David thought it was</i>
<i>the happiest day of his life.</i>

02:14:36.993 --> 02:14:40.121
<i>All the problems</i>
<i>seemed to have disappeared...</i>

02:14:40.230 --> 02:14:42.255
<i>from his mommy's mind.</i>

02:14:42.365 --> 02:14:44.265
<i>There was no Henry,</i>

02:14:44.367 --> 02:14:46.267
<i>there was no Martin,</i>

02:14:46.369 --> 02:14:48.394
<i>there was no grief.</i>

02:14:48.505 --> 02:14:50.405
<i>There was only David.</i>

02:15:00.950 --> 02:15:03.817
<i>David had been warned not</i>
<i>to explain anything to Monica.</i>

02:15:03.920 --> 02:15:07.651
<i>Otherwise, she would become frightened,</i>
<i>and everything would be spoiled.</i>

02:15:07.757 --> 02:15:10.658
<i>But David's journey home</i>
<i>belonged only to him,</i>

02:15:10.760 --> 02:15:13.194
<i>so he didn't see the harm</i>
<i>of painting her pictures of things...</i>

02:15:13.296 --> 02:15:15.196
<i>she would have no memory of.</i>

02:15:43.092 --> 02:15:47.153
<i>David had never had a birthday party</i>
<i>because David had never been born,</i>

02:15:47.263 --> 02:15:50.426
<i>so they baked a cake</i>
<i>and lit some candles.</i>

02:15:50.533 --> 02:15:53.866
- Now, make a wish.
- It came true already

02:16:00.577 --> 02:16:03.546
<i>By now, indeed,</i>
<i>the windows were beginning to dim.</i>

02:16:03.646 --> 02:16:05.546
<i>David drew the shades...</i>

02:16:05.648 --> 02:16:08.617
<i>without even needing</i>
<i>to be asked.</i>

02:16:17.060 --> 02:16:19.255
I really ought to be
tucking you in

02:16:21.130 --> 02:16:23.030
How strange

02:16:25.668 --> 02:16:28.660
How fascinating

02:16:33.977 --> 02:16:36.308
I can hardly keep my eyes open

02:16:38.047 --> 02:16:40.514
I don't know
what's come over me

02:16:46.556 --> 02:16:48.786
Such a beautiful day

02:16:52.028 --> 02:16:54.019
I love you, David

02:17:00.202 --> 02:17:02.296
I do love you

02:17:04.107 --> 02:17:07.008
I have always loved you

02:17:11.246 --> 02:17:14.808
<i>That was the everlasting</i>
<i>moment he had been waiting for.</i>

02:17:17.153 --> 02:17:19.519
<i>And the moment had passed,</i>

02:17:19.621 --> 02:17:21.954
<i>for Monica was sound asleep.</i>

02:17:23.526 --> 02:17:25.619
<i>More than merely asleep.</i>

02:17:27.397 --> 02:17:29.763
<i>Should he shake her,</i>
<i>she would never rouse.</i>

02:17:34.537 --> 02:17:36.437
<i>So David went to sleep too.</i>

02:17:38.374 --> 02:17:42.208
<i>And for the first time</i>
<i>in his life,</i>

02:17:43.680 --> 02:17:45.841
<i>he went to that place...</i>

02:17:47.016 --> 02:17:49.916
<i>where dreams are born.</i>

